<h1>Brian + Wes Meeting Status Report</h1>
<p class="meta"><strong>Meeting date:</strong> May 31, 2026<br>
<strong>Compared against:</strong> main branch, Momentum repository<br>
<strong>Prepared:</strong> June 1, 2026</p>

<h2>Executive Summary</h2>
<p>The meeting&rsquo;s <strong>technical foundation work is largely in place</strong>: ACRCloud is the active song-ID provider, capture no longer blocks on recognition at the end of recording, and there is a <strong>live listening pipeline that starts when the camera preview is ready</strong> (not only after stop).</p>
<p>What remains open is mostly <strong>product policy and UX</strong>: tight geofencing, music-gated posting, playback ticket CTAs, the &ldquo;Become &hellip;&rdquo; onboarding model, and top-of-home messaging. Several meeting decisions were explicitly deferred (Feed vs. Discover rename); those are correctly unchanged in code.</p>
<p><strong>Confidence key:</strong> High = clear in code &bull; Medium = implemented but incomplete vs. notes &bull; Low = process/ops, not verifiable in repo</p>

<h2>1. ACRCloud / Music Recognition</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Meeting item</th><th>Status</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Replace AudD with ACRCloud</td><td class="done">Done</td><td>Worker uses ACRCloud when keys are set (music-recognition.ts, acrcloud-client.ts). AudD token does not activate provider.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Trial + keys + swap in current build</td><td class="done">Done</td><td>ACRCLOUD_* env vars; POST /api/clips/identify-music</td></tr>
<tr><td>POC: identify after recording, fill metadata</td><td class="done">Done</td><td>UploadClip runs identify on caption screen; captureAudioBlob + video snippet fallback</td></tr>
<tr><td>Recognition when camera opens (buffer / pre-listen)</td><td class="done">Done</td><td>QuickRecordButton: startLiveSongPipeline on preview before REC; &ldquo;Listening for music&hellip;&rdquo; UI; 8s segments to ACR via worker</td></tr>
<tr><td>More real-world / simulated testing</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>Manual QA only; no automated venue scenario suite</td></tr>
<tr><td>Research doc / provider comparison</td><td class="notdone">Not in repo</td><td>May live outside git</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Nuances:</strong> Client code still uses &ldquo;AudD&rdquo; naming (auddIdentify.ts) but calls /api/clips/identify-music &rarr; ACRCloud on the worker. Post-capture identify remains as backstop on /upload. handleRecordingComplete navigates immediately with auddPrefill from live match (non-blocking).</p>
<p><strong>Hit list:</strong> Test ACRCloud more &rarr; open (QA). Move recognition earlier &rarr; largely done in code; needs field validation.</p>

<h2>2. Geofencing &amp; Venue Validation</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Meeting item</th><th>Status</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Active product problem; infrastructure</td><td class="partial">Partial</td><td>clips-resolve-show.ts, location_radius_miles, camera prefetch, telemetry (migration 44)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Closest JamBase venue with show tonight</td><td class="done">Done</td><td>Geo /events + same-day enrichment; camera venue/artist preview</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hard geofence (~1 mi) for regular users</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>VENUE_MATCH_RADIUS_FLOOR_MILES = 35 &mdash; matching never tighter than 35 miles</td></tr>
<tr><td>Respect user profile radius</td><td class="partial">Partial</td><td>Profile radius for search; venue match uses max(profile, 35)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dense-city exception</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>No NYC-style multi-venue flow</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dropdown &ldquo;which venue?&rdquo;</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>API returns nearbyVenues (up to 15); UI only auto-applies match === single</td></tr>
<tr><td>Warning UX (&ldquo;seem a little far&hellip;&rdquo;)</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
<tr><td>Block camera if too far</td><td class="notdone">Not done</td><td>Camera opens with GPS; no distance gate</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Hit list:</strong> Define geofence rules, dense-city handling, camera block &mdash; all still open.</p>

